dublin_core.dcvalue: A preliminary study was conducted to evaluate the personality scores of 18 distant healers on the NEO Five Factor Inventory and the Schizotypal Personality Questionnaire Brief These distant healers differed significantly in their schizotypic tendencies both in comparison to normed scores and to a control group of 19 masseurs Further differences were found on scales of Conscientiousness and Openness to experience
Scores for schizotypy and five-factor model of a sample of distant healers: a preliminary study.
